
This directory is intended for PlatformIO Test Runner and project tests.

Unit Testing is a software testing method by which individual units of
source code, sets of one or more MCU program modules together with associated
control data, usage procedures, and operating procedures, are tested to
determine whether they are fit for use. Unit testing finds problems early
in the development cycle.

More information about PlatformIO Unit Testing:
- https://docs.platformio.org/en/latest/advanced/unit-testing/index.html

MIC startup recording helper:

1. Flash the firmware and run the capture script:

   python test/capture_mic_record.py --port COMx

   If no recording starts, keep the script running and reset or power-cycle
   the board. The firmware emits one 10-second mono S16_LE recording after
   the audio path is initialized.

2. The script saves both files into this directory:

   mic_<source>_16000hz_s16le_1ch_<timestamp>.raw
   mic_<source>_16000hz_s16le_1ch_<timestamp>.wav

3. Play the raw file manually if needed:

   ffplay -f s16le -ar 16000 -ac 1 test/mic_<name>.raw
